<section xml:id="sec-code">
  <title>Code Examples</title>

  <p>
    Here is a Python program:
  </p>

  <listing xml:id="listing-hello">
    <caption>Hello World in Python</caption>
    <program language="python">
      <input>

def hello(name):
    print(f"Hello, {name}!")
    return 42

result = hello("world")
      </input>
    </program>
  </listing>

  <p>
    And a Sage computation:
  </p>
  <sage>
    <input>
x = var('x')
f = x^2 + 3*x + 2
f.factor()
    </input>
    <output>(x + 1)*(x + 2)</output>
  </sage>

  <p>
    Inline code like <c>print("hello")</c> should remain inline and not be
    broken across lines.
  </p>

  <p>
    A console session:
  </p>

  <console>
    <prompt>$</prompt>
    <input>echo "hello world"</input>
    <output>hello world</output>
  </console>

  <p>
    A program block with angle brackets:
  </p>

  <program>
      int sum = 0;
      for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j &lt; n; j *= 2) {
          sum = sum + i + j;
        }
      }
  </program>

  <p>
    Fast forward to the end of the animation and then click <c>New Graph</c>
    button to generate a new random graph.
  </p>

  <interactive platform="javascript" design-width="1600" aspect="4:2">
    <script type="module">
      import { DetectCycle } from "./external/interactives/data-structures/entry.js";
      let anim = new DetectCycle({
        zoom: "1.0x",
        // values that are known to produce a cycle on search from 2
        randomSeed: 74919,
        edgePercentage: 0.35
      });
      anim.doDetectCycle();
    </script>

    <xi:include href="../../fragments/ds-graph-instructions.xml"/>
  </interactive>
</section>